    <h1>Customising the user account</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>On this page, you will find all the information about the settings in plentymarkets that you only have to set up once in order to customise your user account. Of course you can change these settings at any time.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="10">1. Setting the complimentary close</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to the <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts</strong> menu and enter a text in the <strong>My account</strong> area. This text is automatically added as a complimentary close at the end of your messages and comments in the ticket system. Generally, this text consists only of a closing and your name. When sending emails from the ticket system, the complimentary close and the signature will automatically be added to the end of the email. You will find a description of how to set up your signature in the next chapter.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting the complimentary close:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>My account</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Complimentary close</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter your complimentary close.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="20">2. Setting the signature</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to the <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts</strong> menu and enter a text in the <strong>My account</strong> area. This text is automatically added as a signature at the end of your messages and comments in the ticket system. Generally, this text consists of your contact details as well as information about where your company is registered and its registration number. Depending on your company’s legal form, the name of the company, the chief executive officer and, if applicable, the European VAT number are all mandatory entries. When sending emails from the ticket system, the complimentary close and the signature will automatically be added to the end of the email.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Template variable for the signature</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The template variables <strong>$Signature</strong> and <strong>$SignatureHTML</strong> contain the complimentary close.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting the signature:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>My account</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Signature</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter your signature.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock warning">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-warning" title="Warning"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Mandatory entries in emails</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Since the beginning of 2007, mandatory entries for email signatures in Germany correspond to those for company business letters. Non-compliance can result in a fine or in a costly warning being issued by a competitor.<br>
Read up on the legal regulations for signatures in your own country or contact a legal adviser for such information.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="30">3. Changing personal settings in the My account area</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to the <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts</strong> menu and open the <strong>My account » Personal settings</strong> area to change the settings of the user currently logged into the system. Therefore, you can only see this tab in your own user account. The tab is divided into 3 tabs with settings that only apply to you personally. These tabs are <strong>General</strong>, <strong>Shortcuts</strong> and <strong>Favourites</strong>.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="40">3.1. Changing general settings</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>General</strong> tab you determine whether you want to receive a warning if tabs are open and you try to close the window. You can also reset all user-specific settings.</p>
</div>
<table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all spread">
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 50%;">
<col style="width: 50%;">
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Button</th>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Explanation</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Reset messages</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Users can deactivate certain messages, e.g. the message that is displayed when plentymarkets needs to be reloaded in order for updates to go into effect. This setting is saved for each individual user. Click on this button again to reset all of the relevant settings for the user. For example, all of the messages that were deactivated will be displayed again.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Reset all</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Resets all of the user-specific settings, e.g. the messages described above, the content and column widths in tables, any favourites, etc.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Warn if tabs are open and the window is to be closed</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Activate</strong> = A warning will be displayed if you try to close a window while tabs are still open.<br>
<strong>Deactivate</strong> = The window will be closed without warning.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><em>Table 1: options in the <strong>Personal settings » General</strong> tab</em></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="50">3.2. Setting up shortcuts</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Default shortcuts are saved in this tab. Shortcuts are used for many functions that are carried out on a regular basis. You can use shortcuts to open important menus in plentymarkets or to switch between tabs and tab levels. For example, the shortcut <strong>Alt + I</strong> opens the item overview. <strong>Alt + W</strong> is used to close the tab again.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Learn more about shortcuts in the following video tutorial:</p>
</div>
<div class="videoblock">
<div class="content">
<iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/99954261" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe>
</div>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Shortcuts are user-specific and some combinations are not possible</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This tab is only visible in your own user account. You are the only person who can edit your shortcuts.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Do not use any shortcut that is specific to an operating system. Shortcuts differ from one operating system to the next. Example: The <strong>F</strong> keys.<br>
The combination <strong>cmd / Ctrl + W</strong> is reserved for the browser and is therefore not possible.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
